==English==
===Etymology===
:Anglo-Saxon ''thunor''

=== Pronunciation ===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: /thŭn'dər/
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /ˈθʌndə(r)/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /"TVnd@(r)/

===Noun===
'''thunder''' (''uncountable'')

#The [[sound]] caused by the discharge of atmospheric electrical charge. 
#:'''Thunder''' ''is preceded by [[lightning]].''
#A sound resembling thunder. 
#:''The noise he thought was '''thunder''' turned out to be the rattle of a sheet of [[aluminum]], struck by trees.''
#A deep, rumbling noise 
#:''Off in the distance, he heard the '''thunder''' of hoofbeats, signalling a [[stampede]].''

